It's simple: You need to find a hash with leading zero's, which is shown as "the difficulty". So, rule of thumb is that you need to find one of 5T keys within 12sec, and then you have your chances of winning... You can also calculate how many guesses you need, since you need to find 5T keys, and if your hashing rate is 100MH/s, you can find it in 50k seconds, which is 14h
So, 1x A6000 @ 5T difficulty = 150h to have a guaranteed key.

Yeah, currently bittensor runs only the text modality according to the standard transformer architecture where text inputs are tokenized (or symbolized efficiently) into token sequences. The length of a standard token sequence is the `sequence_length`, and `batch_size` is the number of token sequences included in a work "package" sent to servers, so a standard request has `sequence_length` x `batch_size` tokens.

The longer the `sequence_length`, the more information and context the server has to produce intelligence, and better models can then outperform more shallow models that don't utilize longer context. Eventually we want to get to a more standard length of 1024 or 2048 tokens per sequence, which will fully utilize typical LLMs of today.
More sequence length means more inputs for model to read and understand the context, right?
correct, usually

So -

Now many jobs come in one batch but smaller inputs so output is not efficient.

You guys plan to send lesser number of jobs to process (batch size) but more input so that model produce quality output.
I think that is the idea yeah, we may possibly reduce batch_size in future to accommodate further sequence length increases, that makes sense.

Cool.

For now, you guys are forcing miners to either level up their hardware to something with better VRAM.

Or change to smaller models.

Does the small models help in quality of output?

No, smaller models probably don't help quality at all, we need bigger models. The Shapley value game theoretics should help to push us in that direction over time, where synergy will be emphasized further and lots of duplicate smaller models with no novelty will be worked out of the system.

So options to miners are -

Get better GPU with more VRAM

Or run finetuned quality models.

Any other?
